   I really enjoyed reading your thoughts on drill and practice software. You bring up some very good points and it was quite interesting to read. I think that Problem Based Learning has significant value for students. However, like you said, "what do we do with the students who lack the most basic skills in a subject area when those skills are necessary for the completion of a collaborative project?" I think that there is time and place for every type of learning strategy. There are definitely benefits to using drill and practice when it will help the student succeed and learn. Thank you for posting your thoughts, great job!
					</p>
