				<div class="blogCommentText">
					<p>
							Does drill and practice deserve its bad reputation? I don't think so. But teachers who rely on drill and practice as a one size fits all solution do earn that bad reputation. Drill and practice has a space at the table for knowledge-level learning and is valuable for building foundational knowledge and skills. I like to think that students can build their confidence during drill and practice exercises and take their knowledge into a more in-depth and collaborative workspace. Nice post on how this plays out in your specific environment.
